ENTRY            40498   20260210   20260319   20260319       4226
SUBENT        40498001   20260210   20260319   20260319       4226
BIB                 14         29
TITLE      More accurate values of total neutron cross-sections
           of 153Eu in the 0.008 - 0.3 eV energy range
AUTHOR     (V.F.Razbudej,A.F.Fedorova,A.V.Muravitskij)
REFERENCE  (R,INDC(CCP)-100,23,1977) Translation of YFI-22
           (R,YFI-22,22,1976)
           (R,KIYAI-75-17,1975)     Experimental details
INSTITUTE  (4UKRIJD)
FACILITY   (REAC,4UKRIJD)  Reactor WWR-M
INC-SOURCE (THCOL)  Thermal column of reactor
SAMPLE      Sample of Eu-153 with admixtures of Eu-151, Gd-155
            and Gd-157, content of Eu-151 obtained from
            activation experiment is (0.652+-0.04)%, gadolinium-
            isotopes content is insignificant.
REL-REF    (M,,V.P.Vertebny+,C,70HELSINKI,1,651,1970)
            Method of definition of Gd isotopes admixtures in
           samples.
METHOD     (ACTIV) Activation method for admixtures determination
DETECTOR   (GELI)  Energy resolution of the detector is 6. keV
MONITOR     No information.
CORRECTION  Corrections on Eu-151 and Gd admixtures were made
COMMENT     Less accurate (uncorrected) data are given earlier
            in (C,71KIEV,2,239,197105), see ENTRY 40109
HISTORY    (19780208C)  Compiled at the centre CJD
           (19981115U)  Corrected at CJD
           (20121127A) M.M. Upper -> lower case correction.
            Subent 002 was corrected.
            BIB information was updated.
           (20260210U) DECAY-DATA: 63-EU-152-M -> 63-EU-152-G in
           Subent 002.  STATUS was corrected fro new rules.
ENDBIB              29
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           32
SUBENT        40498002   20260210   20260319   20260319       4226
BIB                  8         35
REACTION   (63-EU-153(N,TOT),,SIG)
DECAY-DATA (63-EU-152-G,12.4YR)
           (63-EU-154-G,8.6YR,DG,123.1/1274.0)
ANALYSIS    Data measured earlier were revised according to new
           value of admixtures in sample.
COMMENT     Activation analysis was used for determination
            of admixtures only, not for cross-section measurement
ADD-RES    (THEO) Westcott factors for T 293 -403 K are given in
           Table 4 of R,YFI-22,22,1976 .
ERR-ANALYS            Absolute error given in Table 1 is not
            specified by authors. Corresponding relative error is
           in range 2.8 - 0.5 %. So conclusion can be done, that
           it's statistical only.
           (ERR-S)         Statistical error is in range 0.5-2.8%
           as specified by authors.
           (ERR-SYS) Total systematic error was estimated by
           authors as average of two values: 4% ( calculated as
           sum of partial systematic errors) and 2% ( calculated
           as square root of sum of partial errors squared).
                Considered sources of systematical errors:
           (ERR-1,,1.25) Uncertainty of Gd contribution.
           (ERR-2,,1.14) Uncertainty of Eu-151 contribution.
           (ERR-3,,1.1)  Uncertainty of sample sizes.
           (ERR-4,,0.6) Uncertainty of sample weight.
           (ERR-T) Total uncertainty
STATUS     (TABLE,,V.F.Razbudey+,R,INDC(CCP)-100,23,1977)
            Table 1 of R,YFI-22,22,1976 .
           (DEP,40109002) Data of this Subent is revision of data
           given in Subent 40109.002 - see ANALYSIS.
HISTORY    (19981115U)  DATA-ERR changed to ERR-T
           (19981115T)  Coincides with 88028002
           (20121127A) M.M. ERR-ANALYS was corrected essentially.
            Duplicative point at 3.5E-2 eV was deleted.
           (20260210U) Data format E -> F ( as in the article).
            ERR-T -> ERR-S in data block.
ENDBIB              35
COMMON               1          3
ERR-SYS
